This paper deals with the problem of anonymizing datasets, which is a common concern in the field of database management (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the privacy implications of unstructured data such as search engine query logs, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of optimization algorithms to achieve anonymity is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the applicability of the algorithms to a real-world dataset, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG).
